-- INTRODUCTION --------------------------------------------------------------

yardsrvd is a daemon that enables multiple client connections to communicate
with the YARD device developed by A. Weber (see eldo.gotdns.com/yard for 
further information about the hardware). This is done using an UNIX domain
socket.


-- FEATURES ------------------------------------------------------------------

+ Runs as a daemon process
+ Configuration via yardsrvd.conf
+ Up to 5 simultaneous client connections
+ Supports YARD firmware version 4 and up


-- INSTALLATION --------------------------------------------------------------

Refer to the INSTALL file included with this archive for installation
instructions.


-- KNOWN BUGS ----------------------------------------------------------------

Hopefully nothing ;)